Be a student in the 9th, 10th, 11th, or 12th grade;
- Have attended William Mason High School for at least one semester or currently enrolled;
- Have completed at least one semester of rigorous computer science coursework at William Mason High School: Computer Programming I or equivalent (see advisor for clarification) 
- Have earned at least a B in Computer Programming I based on the grading system of the William Mason High School 
- Demonstrate service and leadership and must have 2 MHS teacher/coach recommendations.

The purposes of the National Business Honor Society are to:
 promote and recognize academic achievement in business education at the secondary level;
 foster and recognize leadership skills and character development;
 help members grow ethically and socially by promoting and encouraging an interest in
business; and
 encourage member involvement in service learning initiatives.
